</div>I am aware you cannot lose a level now, hence why I utterly despise the concept of the death changes and bonus xp. WoW or EQ2, honestly does not matter which, I hated the system in both equally. I use wow because it is the more familiar to most, the mechanic is essentially the same though.<br />
<br />
Truth be told, imo the inability to lose a level for being a complete and utter tard straight removes any and all fear of death, Anything shy of you can lose a level flat out for death is not harsh enough to discourage people from being stupid in game.<br />
<br />
However here is what is really eating at me about this whole thing. They are virtually eliminating the need for CR, in case most of you missed this, they are killing two birds with one stone. 1) they are appeasing the ADD kiddies who do not play more then 6 months anyhow before flippantly going to the next great flavor, 2) they are eliminating our argument of stealth being broken by virtue of one of our core tasks being CR. So instead of giving us a stealth that allows us to do so, they are just eliminating the need for it altogether. In my eyes they may as well be killing the rogue class, from a Raid standpoint.<br />
<br />
Frankly I find this whole thing infuriating. It is possible I am overreacting, hence why I am not quitting right now. I am just extremely fustrated and displeased with this idea even being considered by the Devs. I still have another month before my subscription is up, so plenty of time to see how things go.</div>
