    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_380873">All I could think when I'm reading this is...<br />
<br />
&quot;They're going to be screwing with the death system, and they can't even fix it so damage shields and AE's don't break the Rogues combat stance?&quot;  Uhhh... <img src="images/smilies/emote_brow.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Raise Brow" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
I foresee doom.  DOOM.  <img src="images/smilies/emote_alien.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Alien" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
Here's a thought for all you at Sigil reading this:<br />
<br />
Fix the existing bugs before you try to screw with fundamental game-wide mechanics like the death system.  You might actually gain a few subscribers that way before you lose a bunch, instead of just hemorrhaging subs like you are now.<br />
<br />
Here's a quick list that affects everyones gameplay daily, Sigil, in case you forgot:<br />
<ul><li>If you form a group and anyone in the group is not in the same chunk as the inviter/leader, that person will be bugged and/or randomly drop their connection to the group.</li>
<li>If you chunk, you might be dismounted.</li>
<li>If you chunk, any effects you have on you are gone, but they're not really gone.  All the negative aspects of the effect are still there, but all the positive ones are gone.  For example, if you chunk while Stalked, you lose stealth, but you still run slowly. <img src="images/smilies/emote_thumb.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Thumbs Up" class="inlineimg" /></li>
<li>If you chunk, you will appear in the destination chunk facing 180 degrees from the direction you left, causing you to immediately chunk again back to where you were.</li>
<li>If you chunk, your camera will be reset to first person (because first person is SO GREAT. NOT!)</li>
<li>If you chunk, you will crash the destination chunk and be sent back to character select.</li>
<li>If you chunk more than n times, depending on the client graphics/sound settings, your client will crash to desktop</li>
<li>If you have your particle effects set above 50%, your client will randomly BSOD windows (this is a real favorite with the guildmates since the last patch)</li>
<li>If you try to avoid the particle effects BSOD, you have to reset the particle effects slider EVERY TIME YOU LOGIN, because it's not a persistent value, which is really great.  Because frustrating people trying to work around a bug just so they can attempt to play is the best way to retain customers.</li>
<li>Oh, and a personal favorite:  If you abandon the &quot;Blessings of Vengeance&quot; quest (intentionally or accidentally) after receiving one of the blessings, you can never complete the quest line and are locked out of attempting to obtain the best quested weapons in the game, at this time.  Fan-tastic.</li>
</ul>It's like Sigil has two halves.  One half of the dev team is trying desperately to hold onto the vision and doing nothing but continually frustrating the players and losing subs. <br />
<br />
<font size="1"><font color="Plum">This brief interlude of the mind brought to you by the fun folks at &quot;Sarcasm-R-Us&quot; please tip your server on the way out.</font></font><br />
<br />
...  Fade in to maniacal Sigil dev, sitting at his dual 21&quot; LCD monitors, pondering the fate of the redheaded stepchildren of Telon, the Rogues.  He rolls the tips of his fingers on the high polished mahogony desk, and then slams down a fist in a sudden inspiration ...<br />
<br />
<i>Rogues must PAY for their abilities, utility, and fun.  Screw those Rogues out of every copper.  If I see a rich Rogue, I'm taking away Pickpocket! Yarr! I am the big wheel, hear me squeak!  I don't care if no other class has these punitive mechanics, I'm right and the customers are wrong!  Cheap Assembly recipes would mean players would use those abilities, and by GOD we can't have that nonsense!  There should be fear in their hearts and the threat of incontinence in their codpieces before they consume the scroll &quot;Feet Like Cat I&quot;.  That 15 minutes of +10 Dexterity makes them GODS AMONG GNOMES.  I want them to bleed silver and gold before they assemble that poison and feel the love.  Can ya feel the Sigil dev love, Rogues, can ya FEEL IT?  I bet you can!</i><br />
<br />
<font size="1"><font color="Plum">Thank you for watching.  You are now returned to our regularly schedule rant.</font></font><br />
<br />
The other half is proposing things like the death penalty change to get more subs in. Chaos ensues.  Confused customers abound!  Left hand, meet Right hand.  I'm sure you'll both be very happy.<br />
<br />
Whew.  It's early and the vitriol is running high.  Rarr!</div>
