    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_381020">From my understanding 90% of this change is to combat the deluge of CR petitions players are creating because they don't understand the current death system.  In some ways I can appreciate their perspective.  Here are a few i've experienced while in PUGs:<br />
<ul><li>I know I can soulbind my gear but then I wouldn't be able to sell it when I get something better.</li>
<li>*player summons stone at altar* Says to cleric: &quot;Would you res my stone please?&quot;</li>
<li>I know I can summon but don't want to lose xp.</li>
<li>*group wipes at bottom of dungeon* &quot;Everyone has their gear soulbound or an extra set in saddlebag, right?&quot;  One by one: &quot;Huh?&quot;</li>
<li>My personal favorite.  Group member gets summoned while running, quickly runs right into a group of 4dots and gets pwned.  I of course tell player to consent me so I can drag for res.  Player releases and drops group.  *stone disappears*  Shortly thereafter I get a /tell &quot;omg i'm so reporting you guys to a GM for scamming&quot; followed by a global chat &quot;don't group with Pict or anyone with him they're getting you killed then want consent so they can steal your stuff&quot;.</li>
</ul><br />
They need to start small.  I suggest a popup that gives very detailed explanation of the options to the player when they die.  The window could of course be disabled by those of us with half a clue.  The current login message just isn't going to cut it.  Why?<br />
<br />
Me: &quot;Rewroughting armor, Shidreth Mining Camp at the FORGE, 15s a piece.&quot;<br />
<br />
9/10 I get this: &quot;where r u?&quot;<br />
<br />
Ron White said it best: &quot;You can't fix stupid.&quot;</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
